# Tlyarata, Gumbetovsky District, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Tlyarata (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Gumbetovsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 578 as of 2010. There are 8 streets.
Geography
Tlyarata is located 4&nbsp;km east of Mekhelta (the district's administrative centre) by road. Mekhelta and Ingishi are the nearest rural localities.
